-- Ghana, Ivory Coast Collaborate on Cocoa Challenges, Times Says
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2012-01-31T09:33:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/ghana-ivory-coast-collaborate-on-cocoa-challenges-times-says.html
Ghana  and  Ivory Coast  have agreed to
collaborate to find solutions to challenges facing their
respective cocoa industries, the Ghanaian Times reported.  A committee will be set up to identify and recommend
measures to improve productivity, the Accra-based newspaper
said, citing John Henry Martey-Newman, an official at Ghana’s
Presidency. The heads of Ivory Coast and Ghana’s cocoa
industries will jointly chair the committee, the Ghanaian Times
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  